ly a few years before Brock's death, a series of false faces were promoted to serve competing claims and agendas. St-Denis situates Brock’s portraits within an emerging English Canadian imperial nationalism that sought a heroic past which reflected their own aspirations and ambitions. A work of detailed scholarship and a fascinating detective story, The True Face of Sir Isaac Brock details the sometimes petty world of self-proclaimed guardians of the past, the complex process of identification and misidentification that often occurs even at esteemed Canadian institutions, and St-Denis’ own meticulous work as he separates fact from fiction to finally reveal Brock’s true face.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aART / Subjects & Themes / Portraits.2bisacsh  aAgnes FitzGibbon.  aArt Authenticity.  aArt History.  aArt Mystery.  aArt.  aAuthentication.  aBattle of Queenston Heights.  aBrock.  aBrock’s Monument.  aBrock’s Portrait.  aCanadian Art History.  aCanadian War Museum.  aGeneral Brock.  aGerrit Schipper.  aIsaac Brock.  aLudwig Kosche.  aMisidentification.  aPortrait.  aPortraiture.  aReal Isaac Brock.  aSara Mickle.  aTrue Isaac Brock.  aUpper Canada.  aWar of 1812.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773850221?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773850221423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773850221/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles